KNN Model¶

In [52]:
#Finding the optimal K value
no_list = list(range(0,20))
neighbors = list(filter(lambda x: x%2!=0, no_list ))

acc_scores = []

for k in neighbors:
  knn_model = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors= k)
  knn_model.fit(x_train,y_train)
  knn_y_pred = knn_model.predict(x_test)
  score = accuracy_score(y_test,knn_y_pred)

  acc_scores.append(score)

MSE = [1-i for i in acc_scores]

best_k = neighbors[MSE.index(min(MSE))]

print('The optimal k value found is {}' .format(best_k))

sns.lineplot(x=neighbors, y = MSE);
plt.title('MSE v/s k value');
plt.xlabel('K');
plt.ylabel('MSE');

The optimal k value found is 13

def F3():
  global df1,df2
  le = preprocessing.LabelEncoder()
  df2 = pd.DataFrame()
  object_col = df1.columns[pd.Series(df1.columns).apply(lambda x : df1[x].dtype == 'O')]  #hot encoding categorical columns
  for i in df1.columns:
    if i in object_col:
          df2[i] = le.fit_transform(df1[i])
    else:
          df2[i] = df1[i]

  for i in df2.columns:
    if df2[i].dtype == 'O':
        df2[i] = df2[i].astype('category')
    else:
        pass
  df2.dropna(axis=0,inplace= True)

In [86]:
def F5(model, x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test):  
    
    global scores

    model.fit(x_train, y_train)     #training the model

    y_pred = model.predict(x_test)   #testing the model

    cm=confusion_matrix(y_test,y_pred)                #confusion matrix
    a = (cm[0,0] + cm[1,1]) / (cm[0,0] + cm[0,1] + cm[1,0] + cm[1,1])
    p = cm[1,1] / (cm[1,1] + cm[0,1])
    r = cm[1,1] / (cm[1,1] + cm[1,0]) 
    f = (2 * p * r) / (p + r)

    scores = {'accuracy_score' : a,
              'precision' : p,
              'recall' : r,
              'F1-score' : f
               }      
    
    return a,p,r,f

def F6():
  global result
  lr = LogisticRegression()        
  dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=1)   
  br = BaggingClassifier(random_state=1)
  rf = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=1, n_estimators=100)  # loading the models
  gb = GradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=1, n_estimators=100)


  result = {}   # creating an empty dictionary

  # running the mode and model names in loop and appending the result obtained by calling the previous function to fit the data in the model and store the result in empty dictionary
  for model, name  in zip([lr, dt, br, rf, gb], ['Linear Regression', 'Decision Tree',
                                                      'Bagging Ensemble', 'Random Forest', 'Gradient Boost Ensemble']):
      result[name] = F5(model,x_train, x_test,y_train, y_test)
